Unnie.

286
00:25:22,026 --> 00:25:24,696
- Bom!
- Unnie.

287
00:25:27,816 --> 00:25:30,396
Unnie...

288
00:25:30,396 --> 00:25:32,216
It's okay.

289
00:25:34,256 --> 00:25:37,166
I'm so sorry.

290
00:25:38,646 --> 00:25:40,040
It's okay.

291
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:42,850
Unnie, I'm sorry.

292
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:44,746
Unnie...

293
00:25:44,746 --> 00:25:47,226
Everything's fine now.

294
00:25:50,256 --> 00:25:52,156
It's okay.

295
00:25:52,156 --> 00:25:54,176
Everything will be okay.

296
00:26:37,966 --> 00:26:43,426
Dae Beom had the same face as Bom on that night.

297
00:26:44,456 --> 00:26:47,526
It felt like I saw his deepest sorrow.

298
00:27:02,356 --> 00:27:05,896
I decided to stay in Angok.

299
00:27:05,896 --> 00:27:08,596
Also, I decided to work.

300
00:27:10,496 --> 00:27:13,856
For 4.5 hours of work, I get ‚Ç©50,000 ($40) per day,

301
00:27:13,856 --> 00:27:16,996
and I work six days a week.

302
00:27:16,996 --> 00:27:19,956
I start work at 4 a.m.

303
00:27:26,016 --> 00:27:27,836
Oh, my goodness!

304
00:27:31,386 --> 00:27:34,676
At first, it was a burden to wake up early in the morning,

305
00:27:34,676 --> 00:27:38,336
but that's the best part now. Good morning!

306
00:27:39,086 --> 00:27:40,946
Please, have some apples.

307
00:27:40,946 --> 00:27:42,916
Thank you for the apple.

308
00:27:42,916 --> 00:27:47,586
Even if it's the same light, the dusk at the end of day is gloomy,

309
00:27:47,586 --> 00:27:51,826
but the dawn at the start of one's day is refreshing.

310
00:27:53,166 --> 00:27:57,746
It's the same light, but unbelievably different.

311
00:28:01,726 --> 00:28:04,866
When I finish my work, it's 8:30 a.m.

312
00:28:04,866 --> 00:28:08,816
From then, the rest of the day is entirely mine.

313
00:28:09,816 --> 00:28:13,486
I work less and earn the time.

314
00:28:20,066 --> 00:28:24,566
Now I'm living in Bom's house and paying rent.

315
00:28:29,196 --> 00:28:31,936
After paying monthly rent

316
00:28:31,936 --> 00:28:37,226
and using some for living expenses, I had some left so I started saving it.

317
00:28:39,196 --> 00:28:42,056
After Bom and Ha Neul go to school,

318
00:28:42,056 --> 00:28:45,656
I go to the library every day.

319
00:28:45,656 --> 00:28:49,376
I said you need to upload it every day before leaving work.

320
00:28:49,376 --> 00:28:54,386
How many times did I say book usage data can't be uploaded just once a week?

321
00:28:54,386 --> 00:28:58,566
But, Sunbaenim, that young lady is our only customer.

322
00:28:58,566 --> 00:29:01,496
What's the point of uploading data daily?

323
00:29:01,496 --> 00:29:03,596
You complain too much for a civil servant.

324
00:29:03,596 --> 00:29:06,146
I didn't expect to be stuck in this place!

325
00:29:14,256 --> 00:29:15,866
Unnie.

326
00:29:20,526 --> 00:29:23,306
Where's the real estate agency in this town?

327
00:29:24,766 --> 00:29:27,136
I'm not an "unnie."

328
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:35,110
These days, I got into hand-copying books

329
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:38,576
so I handwrite books that I like.

330
00:29:38,576 --> 00:29:43,656
I feel it empties my worry and fills my soul.

331
00:29:45,096 --> 00:29:49,026
When the library closes, we two go for a jog.

332
00:29:49,026 --> 00:29:54,536
Dae Beom switched the morning jogging to evening jogging for me.

333
00:29:54,536 --> 00:29:58,726
We usually talk while jogging.

334
00:29:58,726 --> 00:30:02,936
Every day is rather similar, but there are endless things to discuss.

335
00:30:02,936 --> 00:30:07,056
I think Dae Beom definitely talks more than I do lately.

336
00:30:07,056 --> 00:30:10,956
- It's not as hard as before.
- I think you're a better runner now than I am.

337
00:30:10,956 --> 00:30:13,476
Maybe I am.

338
00:30:13,476 --> 00:30:16,236
Okay, so now that you've reviewed it, what do you think?

339
00:30:16,236 --> 00:30:21,636
I read this, and this was very, very interesting that you sent me.

340
00:30:21,636 --> 00:30:23,906
But...

341
00:30:23,906 --> 00:30:27,466
Dae Beom started to work again with the Netherlands' professor.

342
00:30:27,466 --> 00:30:30,016
Explain by calculating it.

343
00:30:30,016 --> 00:30:31,036
Why is that?

344
00:30:31,036 --> 00:30:35,106
The Netherlands' professor said family is more important for him than work.

345
00:30:35,106 --> 00:30:37,366
- So he proposed working together, like hanging out.
- I do want to see.

346
00:30:37,366 --> 00:30:41,076
- And Dae Beom was impressed by his words so he decided to work with him.
- Am I wrong?

347
00:30:41,076 --> 00:30:43,456
No, I mean, that was a difficult one.

348
00:30:43,456 --> 00:30:49,146
- He said he's working from the beginning with the Netherlands' professor.
- I'll see it so...

349
00:30:49,146 --> 00:30:51,456
Well, I don't think it was difficult at all.

350
00:30:51,456 --> 00:30:56,916
Actually, I have a problem that is much more difficult to solve.

351
00:30:56,916 --> 00:30:58,776
Like what?

352
00:31:00,006 --> 00:31:01,916
My wife!

353
00:31:12,526 --> 00:31:14,756
- Unnie.
- Yes?

354
00:31:14,756 --> 00:31:17,476
There's something I want to do with you.

355
00:31:17,476 --> 00:31:19,366
What is it?

356
00:31:19,366 --> 00:31:23,506
But can you promise me first that you'll do it with me?

357
00:31:23,506 --> 00:31:27,376
I think I really can't do it by myself.

358
00:31:27,376 --> 00:31:29,476
What is it for you to say so?

359
00:31:29,476 --> 00:31:32,526
Noona, don't get involved in this; ignore her.

360
00:31:32,526 --> 00:31:34,516
It is...

361
00:31:37,976 --> 00:31:39,796
this thing.

362
00:31:41,076 --> 00:31:43,436
What's this?
[A Competition for Webtoon Proposals]

363
00:31:46,356 --> 00:31:48,006
"A competition for Webtoon proposals"?

364
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:50,976
Yes. But Unnie, this is the crazy part.

365
00:31:50,976 --> 00:31:53,166
The winner's prize is 100 million won ($79,000).

366
00:31:53,166 --> 00:31:55,146
Isn't that amazing?

367
00:31:55,146 --> 00:31:57,446
But why do you want to do this with me?

368
00:31:57,446 --> 00:32:00,956
I mean, I can draw, but I'm not good at writing.

369
00:32:00,956 --> 00:32:04,366
But you worked in a publishing company before and read many books.

370
00:32:04,366 --> 00:32:06,606
So you will write the story, and I will draw.

371
00:32:06,606 --> 00:32:08,406
No, I can't!

372
00:32:08,406 --> 00:32:11,316
You know how much I dread writing.

373
00:32:11,316 --> 00:32:13,226
Unnie, please!

374
00:32:13,226 --> 00:32:16,386
You wrote an article about a grandmother with Oppa Dae Beom before.

375
00:32:16,386 --> 00:32:20,086
But this and that are completely different things.

376
00:32:20,086 --> 00:32:24,056
Just ignore her idea. She has such false hope. You are not even good at drawing!

377
00:32:24,056 --> 00:32:26,616
Seriously! What do you know about my drawing?

378
00:32:26,616 --> 00:32:28,836
I'll do the dishes.

379
00:32:28,836 --> 00:32:32,516
Unnie, let's just try one time. Pretty please!

380
00:32:32,516 --> 00:32:35,666
No, I can't do it. Focus on your food.

381
00:32:35,666 --> 00:32:38,656
Please, do it with me!

382
00:32:39,546 --> 00:32:43,606
Jo Ji Young, you've been acting weird lately. Why are you eating meals with us all the time?

383
00:32:43,606 --> 00:32:46,020
Also, you should call me before coming over!

384
00:32:46,020 --> 00:32:49,600
Then I would prepare more food.

385
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,576
This is enough for me.

386
00:32:52,816 --> 00:32:57,196
Now I found a place in Seoul, all that's left is moving my stuff.

387
00:32:57,196 --> 00:32:59,866
Are you here to ask me to pack your stuff?

388
00:32:59,866 --> 00:33:01,746
Pack what stuff?

389
00:33:05,106 --> 00:33:11,626
I already prepared boxes and the truck to move your stuff so don't worry.

390
00:33:11,626 --> 00:33:14,986
What? I didn't even think about that.

391
00:33:18,536 --> 00:33:20,936
We are eating this together.

392
00:33:21,756 --> 00:33:23,436
I'm sorry.

393
00:33:23,436 --> 00:33:25,530
You are better than your dad.

394
00:33:26,506 --> 00:33:28,546
You guys were having a meal together.

395
00:33:28,546 --> 00:33:30,526
Oh, hello?

396
00:33:30,526 --> 00:33:32,436
Seong Min, the thing is...

397
00:33:32,436 --> 00:33:33,726
Why? Do you need some help?

398
00:33:33,726 --> 00:33:36,466
No, it's not like that.

399
00:33:36,466 --> 00:33:39,986
I wanted to ask for the phone number of the young lady from the billiards.

400
00:33:39,986 --> 00:33:42,066
Yeo Reum?

401
00:33:42,066 --> 00:33:45,546
It's good you are here, too, Manager Jo.

402
00:33:45,546 --> 00:33:49,156
Can you give a message to Dae Beom?

403
00:33:49,156 --> 00:33:51,726
About what?

404
00:33:51,726 --> 00:33:56,676
I didn't have a chance to thank them properly.

405
00:33:56,676 --> 00:34:01,256
I want to treat them to dinner at our restaurant.

406
00:34:01,256 --> 00:34:04,306
- Oh, really?
- That's a great idea!

407
00:34:04,306 --> 00:34:10,316
But while you're at it, do you have any intention of throwing a bigger party?

408
00:34:10,316 --> 00:34:11,966
How?

409
00:34:11,966 --> 00:34:13,176
Beef.

410
00:34:13,176 --> 00:34:17,566
- Beef! Beef!
- Yes! Yes!

411
00:34:17,566 --> 00:34:20,746
- Jun, come over for a beef party.
- Hooray!

412
00:34:21,366 --> 00:34:22,876
Please come to the party later. Call me!

413
00:34:22,876 --> 00:34:25,336
- See you later!
- You, too.

414
00:34:28,426 --> 00:34:31,836
Then let's take Ha Neul as well.

415
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,986
Why would you want Ha Neul to join? Let him just focus on studying.

416
00:34:34,986 --> 00:34:36,746
Why?

417
00:34:36,746 --> 00:34:41,006
Why? He didn't even go on the valley trip. I think he'll say he won't come.

418
00:34:41,006 --> 00:34:43,186
Oh, that's right. Bom.

419
00:34:43,186 --> 00:34:44,696
Yes?

420
00:34:44,696 --> 00:34:49,520
Are you no longer in contact with Jae Hoon?

421
00:34:50,366 --> 00:34:52,376
I'm asking...

422
00:34:53,356 --> 00:34:56,826
I was so surprised when I saw this text from him.

423
00:34:58,266 --> 00:35:02,356
[Jae Hoon: Noona, I'm going to America. Please take good care of Bom.]

424
00:35:06,106 --> 00:35:09,636
I don't know what happened between you two.

425
00:35:09,636 --> 00:35:12,616
But Jae Hoon likes you a lot.

426
00:35:13,596 --> 00:35:15,706
You know that, right?

427
00:35:15,706 --> 00:35:18,406
Let's not talk about him anymore.

428
00:35:19,636 --> 00:35:21,656
Okay.

429
00:35:23,546 --> 00:35:25,866
- Unnie.
- Yes?

430
00:35:25,866 --> 00:35:29,846
It would be great if we win the contest and get the 100 million won.

431
00:35:29,846 --> 00:35:32,416
What do you want to do if you get that money?

432
00:35:32,416 --> 00:35:34,266
Well...

433
00:35:40,006 --> 00:35:42,496
I miss my grandmother.

434
00:35:56,166 --> 00:36:00,976
If Bom draws with what I wrote, I think it'll fail.

435
00:36:00,976 --> 00:36:02,486
No.

436
00:36:02,486 --> 00:36:06,126
I'm really not good at writing. You know that.

437
00:36:06,126 --> 00:36:09,036
I don't know about that.

438
00:36:09,036 --> 00:36:10,836
You're just saying that.

439
00:36:13,446 --> 00:36:15,716
If I tell you honestly,

440
00:36:15,716 --> 00:36:18,896
I think I'm very similar to you.

441
00:36:18,896 --> 00:36:21,316
What's similar?

442
00:36:21,316 --> 00:36:26,286
I get very nervous I might be wrong when I'm solving math problems.

443
00:36:26,286 --> 00:36:29,006
But one day, the Netherlands' professor

444
00:36:29,006 --> 00:36:35,316
gave a wrong answer and simply said, "Oh, my gosh!"

445
00:36:35,316 --> 00:36:37,386
Really?

446
00:36:39,496 --> 00:36:42,176
For me,

447
00:36:42,176 --> 00:36:45,906
I enjoy conversing with you so much.

448
00:36:51,176 --> 00:36:55,276
So I decided to write a story.

449
00:36:55,276 --> 00:36:57,876
Why can't I think of anything?

450
00:36:59,496 --> 00:37:01,446
Gyeo Wool!

451
00:37:01,446 --> 00:37:05,386
I'm going to develop a white-page phobia.

452
00:37:10,466 --> 00:37:13,936
But it was difficult like I expected.

453
00:37:13,936 --> 00:37:17,026
What should I do?

454
00:37:18,856 --> 00:37:20,536
What did you say?

455
00:37:20,536 --> 00:37:23,596
"Just do it since I'm not good at it anyway"?

456
00:37:26,016 --> 00:37:28,156
You're right.

457
00:37:28,156 --> 00:37:30,496
How did you know that?

458
00:37:31,706 --> 00:37:33,526
Okay.

459
00:37:38,366 --> 00:37:41,206
What if I go to Hollywood with this?

460
00:37:46,896 --> 00:37:50,066
I can't go anywhere with this!

461
00:37:50,066 --> 00:37:53,646
Bom, I'm sorry!

462
00:37:54,356 --> 00:37:56,526
I would like to pay for these.

463
00:38:00,796 --> 00:38:03,556
I'm not a genius.

464
00:38:03,556 --> 00:38:06,876
Let's admit that first and start the work.

465
00:38:08,366 --> 00:38:10,346
I'm just an ordinary human.

466
00:38:10,346 --> 00:38:14,366
No, I might be lacking a bit.

467
00:38:16,556 --> 00:38:18,956
No matter what, live every day.

468
00:38:18,956 --> 00:38:23,026
That's the only thing I can do about it.

469
00:38:28,296 --> 00:38:31,126
- Oh, what is it?
- You surprised me!

470
00:38:31,126 --> 00:38:32,416
When did you come home?

471
00:38:32,416 --> 00:38:36,116
You are good at writing, but you said you couldn't.

472
00:38:36,116 --> 00:38:39,586
Did you read it? You couldn't see it, right?

473
00:38:39,586 --> 00:38:44,166
But isn't the main character too old? How can I draw a woman with a child?

474
00:38:44,166 --> 00:38:48,316
No, I just wrote this as a test.

475
00:38:48,316 --> 00:38:50,096
- It's not like that...
- Let me read it again.

476
00:38:50,096 --> 00:38:51,716
- No!
- Let me see!

477
00:38:51,716 --> 00:38:53,536
Someone's at the front door.

478
00:38:53,536 --> 00:38:55,336
Who would that be?

479
00:38:56,136 --> 00:38:58,326
Who is it?

480
00:39:02,566 --> 00:39:04,576
Jae Hoon!

481
00:39:04,576 --> 00:39:05,916
Heo Jae Hoon.

482
00:39:05,916 --> 00:39:08,866
Bom, Noona.

483
00:39:08,866 --> 00:39:10,666
Have you been well?

484
00:39:10,666 --> 00:39:13,236
Didn't you go back to America?

485
00:39:13,236 --> 00:39:15,346
I did.

486
00:39:15,346 --> 00:39:17,596
But...

487
00:39:17,596 --> 00:39:20,066
I thought a lot while I was over there.

488
00:39:20,066 --> 00:39:23,146
Then did you go to America and come back here?

489
00:39:23,146 --> 00:39:25,506
Yes, Bom.

490
00:39:27,196 --> 00:39:29,326
While I was away from you,

491
00:39:29,326 --> 00:39:32,496
I thought a lot about myself.

492
00:39:32,496 --> 00:39:34,306
Heo Jae Hoon, are you out of your mind?

493
00:39:34,306 --> 00:39:38,066
Is America right next door? Do you know how much plane tickets cost?

494
00:39:38,066 --> 00:39:42,566
Can you let me talk? Please don't cut me off.

495
00:39:42,566 --> 00:39:45,746
Okay. I'm sorry.

496
00:39:45,746 --> 00:39:49,466
I thought deeply about my life.

497
00:39:49,466 --> 00:39:52,326
I thought of what I truly wanted.

498
00:39:52,326 --> 00:39:56,046
I thought of what I should live for.

499
00:39:56,046 --> 00:40:00,166
After pondering those things, I returned here.

500
00:40:00,166 --> 00:40:03,826
Really? Why did you come here?

501
00:40:03,826 --> 00:40:05,356
I came here to marry you.

502
00:40:05,356 --> 00:40:07,026
What!

503
00:40:07,726 --> 00:40:11,056
M-Marriage? Are you crazy?

504
00:40:11,056 --> 00:40:14,976
So please give me your sincere answer as well.

505
00:40:14,976 --> 00:40:18,046
Should I go back to America?

506
00:40:21,266 --> 00:40:24,176
But we are too young to get married.

507
00:40:24,176 --> 00:40:26,826
I'm serious right now.

508
00:40:26,826 --> 00:40:29,346
Stop avoiding and answer my question.

509
00:40:31,016 --> 00:40:33,806
Do you hate that I came back?

510
00:40:34,926 --> 00:40:37,716
It's not that I dislike it.

511
00:40:38,636 --> 00:40:43,746
But we should date properly before discussing marriage.

512
00:40:43,746 --> 00:40:45,706
Is that so?

513
00:40:45,706 --> 00:40:47,856
Then shall we do that?

514
00:40:47,856 --> 00:40:50,696
I didn't mean we should get married right now.

515
00:40:50,696 --> 00:40:55,006
Are you kidding me again? Stop it.

516
00:40:56,146 --> 00:40:58,566
Jae Hoon.

517
00:40:58,566 --> 00:41:00,106
It's so good to see you again.

518
00:41:00,106 --> 00:41:01,976
Noona.

519
00:41:02,706 --> 00:41:04,146
You did good.

520
00:41:04,146 --> 00:41:05,946
Thank you.

521
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:13,676
I missed you so much.

522
00:41:13,676 --> 00:41:15,416
Yes, me, too.

523
00:41:15,416 --> 00:41:17,486
Gyeo Wool!

524
00:41:21,536 --> 00:41:23,496
Who is this guy?

525
00:41:23,496 --> 00:41:27,806
- Well...
- Hello, I'm your brother-in-law.

526
00:41:27,806 --> 00:41:32,286
What? Are you really out of your mind?

527
00:41:32,286 --> 00:41:34,356
He's my young brother-in-law.

528
00:41:34,356 --> 00:41:37,436
Seriously, stop it!

529
00:41:38,606 --> 00:41:40,546
- Is it good?
- It's incredible!

530
00:41:40,546 --> 00:41:43,706
Of course, it'll be.

531
00:41:45,416 --> 00:41:46,916
Hyung!

532
00:41:46,916 --> 00:41:49,026
- Oh, Unnie!
- We are here.

533
00:41:49,026 --> 00:41:51,716
- Come on!
- Welcome! Have a seat.

534
00:41:51,716 --> 00:41:53,546
I bet you must be hungry.

535
00:41:53,546 --> 00:41:55,356
Thank you so much for the food.

536
00:41:55,356 --> 00:41:57,556
Jun, you, too. Come and sit.

537
00:41:57,556 --> 00:41:59,706
That's right, Jun.

538
00:41:59,706 --> 00:42:02,266
Geun Ho is now going to school!

539
00:42:02,266 --> 00:42:04,826
Wow, amazing!

540
00:42:04,826 --> 00:42:07,126
- My Geun Ho now goes to school!
- Great news!

541
00:42:07,126 --> 00:42:11,576
This beef's marbling is no joke. Eat as much as you want!

542
00:42:11,576 --> 00:42:13,446
You should also eat now.

543
00:42:13,446 --> 00:42:15,956
- Yeo Reum, Dae Beom.
- Yes?

544
00:42:15,956 --> 00:42:20,366
I'm so grateful to you two.

545
00:42:20,366 --> 00:42:22,106
It's nothing.

546
00:42:22,106 --> 00:42:25,066
What do you mean "it's nothing"? Please, enjoy the food.

547
00:42:25,066 --> 00:42:27,956
Thank you for the food!

548
00:42:27,956 --> 00:42:31,126
- Thank you for the food!
- Uncle, Uncle!

549
00:42:31,126 --> 00:42:35,496
But weren't Unnie Yeo Reum and Oppa Dae Beom the stars of tonight?

550
00:42:35,496 --> 00:42:37,486
What's that?

551
00:42:37,486 --> 00:42:39,846
Oh, seriously!
[Congratulations to Manager Jo Ji Young on moving to Seoul!]

552
00:42:39,846 --> 00:42:44,046
It's nice to celebrate good things together with good people. Shall we read it together?

553
00:42:44,046 --> 00:42:48,926
Congratulations to Manager Jo Ji Young on moving to Seoul!

554
00:42:48,926 --> 00:42:52,726
- Seriously!
- She's leaving Angok!

555
00:42:52,726 --> 00:42:55,576
What's wrong with him?

556
00:42:55,576 --> 00:42:58,456
Jun, eat as much as you want!

557
00:42:58,456 --> 00:43:01,876
Yes, I'll eat a lot. Thanks for the food!

558
00:43:01,876 --> 00:43:03,496
- Shall we eat as well?
- Thanks for the food.

559
00:43:03,496 --> 00:43:05,546
- Thank you for the food!
- Enjoy!

560
00:43:05,546 --> 00:43:08,226
Do you want greens for the meat?

561
00:43:08,226 --> 00:43:10,236
It's so good.

562
00:43:10,236 --> 00:43:12,606
Go ahead and eat before it gets cold.

563
00:43:12,606 --> 00:43:15,126
Jae Hoon, eat the meat.

564
00:43:17,186 --> 00:43:20,056
- Eat as much as you want.
- Thank you.

565
00:43:30,036 --> 00:43:32,336
You're so good at it!

566
00:43:32,336 --> 00:43:35,276
Come! Come to the stage!

567
00:43:52,186 --> 00:43:55,356
I thought about what "happiness" means.

568
00:43:56,496 --> 00:43:59,106
When I searched it in the dictionary,

569
00:43:59,106 --> 00:44:03,236
it means you feel content with enough satisfaction and joy in your life

570
00:44:03,236 --> 00:44:06,936
or such a state.

571
00:44:08,216 --> 00:44:13,126
Since that was so long, I shortened it.

572
00:44:14,546 --> 00:44:16,956
"Happiness":

573
00:44:16,956 --> 00:44:20,036
"The state where you lack nothing."

574
00:44:25,526 --> 00:44:28,686
I thought about today.

575
00:44:28,686 --> 00:44:31,426
Through the air that chills at dawn now,

576
00:44:31,426 --> 00:44:34,996
I rode my bicycle down the streets before the sun rose.

577
00:44:34,996 --> 00:44:36,976
I felt content.

578
00:44:37,856 --> 00:44:39,806
It is enough.

579
00:44:45,236 --> 00:44:49,706
I came home thirsty and drank water.

580
00:44:49,706 --> 00:44:54,536
I remembered Grandma's remark that water is the tastiest thing in the world.

581
00:44:56,636 --> 00:44:58,496
It was true.

582
00:44:58,496 --> 00:45:00,576
It is enough.

583
00:45:05,286 --> 00:45:10,286
I like the snapping sound when I hang the laundry on the line.

584
00:45:10,286 --> 00:45:15,036
Also, I like the smell of detergent left on my hands.

585
00:45:15,036 --> 00:45:17,036
It is enough.

586
00:45:22,696 --> 00:45:26,246
In the library, the afternoon sun felt like a drug;

587
00:45:26,246 --> 00:45:28,586
I dozed off a little bit.

588
00:45:28,586 --> 00:45:30,816
It was a sweet nap.

589
00:45:30,816 --> 00:45:32,866
It is enough.

590
00:45:34,336 --> 00:45:40,746
Standing before a bookcase, it's always fun to think what to read.

591
00:45:40,746 --> 00:45:42,740
It's exciting.

592
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,250
["The Beautiful Truth" by Kim Seong Hyeon]

593
00:45:44,250 --> 00:45:46,266
It is enough.

594
00:45:51,586 --> 00:45:54,250
Whenever Bom and I lie down for bed,

595
00:45:54,250 --> 00:45:57,276
we always laugh until our stomachs hurt.

596
00:45:57,276 --> 00:46:00,816
Sometimes it's funny just looking into each other's eyes.

597
00:46:00,816 --> 00:46:02,776
It is enough.

598
00:46:05,856 --> 00:46:08,476
What should I do then?

599
00:46:14,646 --> 00:46:17,366
Bom, wake up.

600
00:46:21,856 --> 00:46:23,686
It's okay.

601
00:46:24,706 --> 00:46:26,666
Bom told me,

602
00:46:26,666 --> 00:46:27,646
"It's okay."

603
00:46:27,646 --> 00:46:31,136
When I said, "Everything's okay," on that day,

604
00:46:31,136 --> 00:46:37,116
surprisingly, it really felt like everything would be fine.

605
00:46:37,116 --> 00:46:38,976
I also felt the same way.

606
00:46:38,976 --> 00:46:45,836
When I said, "Everything's okay," it really felt like all would be okay.

607
00:46:49,626 --> 00:46:51,986
Wow, feel the wind.

608
00:46:51,986 --> 00:46:54,806
Unnie, I think it's really autumn now, isn't it?

609
00:46:54,806 --> 00:46:56,636
I think so, too.

610
00:46:57,426 --> 00:46:59,796
Can I tell you something surprising?

611
00:46:59,796 --> 00:47:01,576
What is it?

612
00:47:02,596 --> 00:47:04,446
Bom (Spring),

613
00:47:04,446 --> 00:47:06,536
Yeo Reum (Summer),

614
00:47:06,536 --> 00:47:08,056
autumn (in the air),

615
00:47:08,056 --> 00:47:09,416
and Gyeo Wool (Winter)!

616
00:47:09,416 --> 00:47:12,786
- You're right!
- All four seasons are here now.

617
00:47:22,616 --> 00:47:29,316
Goodbye to my first summer in Angok.

618
00:47:38,636 --> 00:47:41,616
It really feels weird.

619
00:47:45,936 --> 00:47:49,706
I'm leaving soon. Do you feel okay?

620
00:47:49,706 --> 00:47:55,086
Ji Young, waiting for you is my hobby, and I'm best at it.

621
00:47:55,916 --> 00:47:58,466
I may meet a man if you keep waiting.

622
00:47:59,376 --> 00:48:02,656
- If you want to, go for it!
- No.

623
00:48:03,376 --> 00:48:05,946
Hey, you live for the fun of criticizing others,

624
00:48:05,946 --> 00:48:09,306
and how can you find a better man than me who is easily criticized?

625
00:48:09,306 --> 00:48:13,516
I act like this only with you. Do you think I'd be like this to others?

626
00:48:13,516 --> 00:48:17,586
You are the one who makes me angry the most!

627
00:48:17,586 --> 00:48:19,986
Or you can go and return like me (getting married and divorced).

628
00:48:19,986 --> 00:48:22,616
I will still like you even so.

629
00:48:24,656 --> 00:48:26,536
Go where?

630
00:48:29,896 --> 00:48:32,306
Are you out of your mind?

631
00:48:32,306 --> 00:48:34,716
Unless you're crazy, how can you say that?

632
00:48:34,716 --> 00:48:37,386
- Jun might wake up.
- How can you say that in front of a child?

633
00:48:37,386 --> 00:48:39,916
Take back what you said. Take it back!

634
00:48:43,006 --> 00:48:44,396
Jun woke up!

635
00:48:44,396 --> 00:48:48,076
- He woke up due to you!
- Oh my.

636
00:48:54,806 --> 00:48:57,486
What are you doing for this week's day off?

637
00:48:57,486 --> 00:48:59,946
Why? Do you want to go out for delicious food again?

638
00:48:59,946 --> 00:49:03,676
No, I was going to say, "Let's see Dae Ho."

639
00:49:03,676 --> 00:49:06,456
What? Dae Ho?

640
00:49:06,456 --> 00:49:08,976
You told me to be friends with him.

641
00:49:08,976 --> 00:49:11,266
I guess you matured a bit.

642
00:49:16,866 --> 00:49:18,596
- What was that?
- What?

643
00:49:18,596 --> 00:49:20,996
I wanted to play hard to get sometimes, too.

644
00:49:20,996 --> 00:49:23,446
It feels great after doing so.

645
00:49:23,446 --> 00:49:28,036
How dare you play hard to get?

646
00:49:28,036 --> 00:49:29,366
It's so much fun playing hard to get!

647
00:49:29,366 --> 00:49:32,016
Come over here! Gyeo Wool, go get him!

648
00:49:32,016 --> 00:49:33,976
Give Gyeo Wool back to me!

649
00:49:33,976 --> 00:49:35,626
- Come here!
- Hurry, catch me.

650
00:49:35,626 --> 00:49:38,876
Gyeo Wool, go and bite him!

651
00:49:38,876 --> 00:49:41,666
Gyeo Wool, look at this. Look over here!

652
00:49:41,666 --> 00:49:42,946
Stop it!

653
00:49:42,946 --> 00:49:46,286
- Dae Beom.
- Yes?

654
00:49:46,286 --> 00:49:50,076
Do you ever regret staying here?

655
00:49:50,946 --> 00:49:53,166
I don't regret it.

656
00:49:53,166 --> 00:49:55,166
What about you, Yeo Reum?

657
00:49:57,386 --> 00:49:59,326
Me, neither.

658
